{"word":"τρέμω","slug":"τρέμω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>τρέμω</b></el> <p/><a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> <el>tremo, to tremble, quake, quiver</el>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>:—<a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:infinitive'>inf.</a> <i>to tremble</i> or <i>fear to</i> do, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>: —<a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> <i>to tremble at, fear</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/>"}]}